# Mailchimp Growth Strategist — example crontab entry
#
# Add to your user crontab via `crontab -e`:
#
# Monday 7am Pacific Time = 14:00 UTC (PST winter) or 15:00 UTC (PDT summer).
# Pick the one matching your current TZ, or use a TZ-aware wrapper.
#
# Format: m h dom mon dow command
#
# Mon 7am PT (handle both PST/PDT correctly: rely on the system's local TZ):

0 7 * * 1   cd /Users/dprabhakara/cursor/mailchimp-growth-strategist && bash scripts/run_weekly.sh > /tmp/mc-growth-cron.log 2>&1

# That command:
#   1. Prepares the weekly run dir and prints the orchestrator-invocation prompt.
#   2. Output is logged to /tmp/mc-growth-cron.log.
#
# To actually invoke the agent, you have two options:
#
# Option A (manual): receive the cron output as a notification, then paste the
# orchestrator prompt into a Cursor chat.
#
# Option B (automated): wrap with `cursor agent --headless` (if/when Cursor CLI
# supports headless invocations of skills). Example draft:
#
#   0 7 * * 1   cd /Users/dprabhakara/cursor/mailchimp-growth-strategist && \
#               bash scripts/run_weekly.sh && \
#               cursor agent --headless "Run mailchimp-growth-strategist orchestrator for $(date +%G-W%V)"
#
# Option C (background subagent): trigger via `cursor agent` from a Cursor
# `sessionStart` hook so it's prompted whenever you open Cursor on a Monday.
# See .cursor/hooks.json + .cursor/hooks/check-weekly.sh in this repo.
